<author><name><![CDATA[Shehzad Sattar]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-07-11T13:20:42+01:00</updated>
<published>2017-07-11T13:20:42+01:00</published>
<id>https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1471&amp;p=1572#p1572</id>
<link href="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1471&amp;p=1572#p1572"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Ahl al-Hadith; Ittiba, Taqlid &amp; Madhhabs • I Am Follower Of My Madhab, I Don't Have Any Concern With Hadith]]></title>

<category term="The Ahl al-Hadith; Ittiba, Taqlid &amp; Madhhabs" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=11" label="The Ahl al-Hadith; Ittiba, Taqlid &amp; Madhhabs"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1471&amp;p=1572#p1572"><![CDATA[
I Am Follower Of My Madhab, I Don't Have Any Concern With Hadith<br /><br />Allamah at-Taybee (743h) Author of Sharah Mishkaat said<br />في هذا الحديث توبيخ وتقريع نشأ من عظيم على من ترك السنة والعمل با لحديث, استغناء عنها بالكتاب, هذا مع الكتاب فكيف بمن رجح الرأي على الحديث؟ وإذا سمع حديثا من الأحاديث الصحيحة قال: لا علي بأن أعمل بها, فإن لي مذهبا أتبعه<br /><br />In this hadeeth there is great scolding and bashing for the one who leaves Sunnah... and when he hears the hadith from authentic ahadeeth he says: I do not have to practice on it, I am follower of my Madhab.<br /><br />[Sharah Mishkaat at-Taybee 2/631 Maktabah tul Shamela, Hashiyah al-Sindhee Ibn Majah vol 1 page 3, Tuhfah tul Hawdi Kitab al-Ilm under the hadeeth no. 2664]<br /><br />Translated by Asim ul Haqq<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Tue Jul 11, 2017 1:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
